N = np.array([100, 1000, 10000])
#Theoretical means
miu = N/20

#Theoratical Standard Deviation
sigma = ((N/20)*(1-(1/20)))**0.5

for i in range(len(N)):
    plt.figure()
    x = np.linspace(0,1,10)
    y = np.ones(10)*miu[i]
    uni = np.random.rand(N[i])
    sns.distplot(uni, hist=True, kde=False,\
                 bins=20, color = 'blue',\
                 hist_kws={'edgecolor':'black'})
    plt.plot(x,y,color='red',label='Mean')
    plt.plot(x,y+3*sigma[i],color='blue',label='+3 SD')
    plt.plot(x,y-3*sigma[i],color='green',label='-3 SD')
    plt.title('Uniformly Distrubuted Random Variables (N = %d)' % N[i])
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    lgd = plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)
    plt.savefig('Q1-10Fig%d'%fc, bbox_extra_artists=(lgd,), bbox_inches='tight'); fc += 1

N = np.array([100, 1000, 10000])

def theo_counts(binedges,N):
    mean = []
    mean_min = []
    mean_plu = []
    for i in range(1,len(binedges)):
        p = (normalsci.cdf(binedges[i])-normalsci.cdf(binedges[i-1]))
        mean.append(N*p)
        mean_min.append(N*(p)-3*(N*(p)*(1-p))**0.5)
        mean_plu.append(N*(p)+3*(N*(p)*(1-p))**0.5)
    mean.append(0)
    mean_min.append(0)
    mean_plu.append(0)
    return mean, mean_plu, mean_min


for i in range(len(N)):
    norm = np.random.randn(N[i])
    plt.figure()   
    data = np.histogram(norm, bins=20, density=True)
    sns.distplot(norm, hist=True, kde=False,\
                 bins=data[1], color = 'blue',\
                 hist_kws={'edgecolor':'black'})
    mean, mean_plu, mean_min = theo_counts(data[1],N[i])
    plt.step(data[1],mean,where='post', color ='red',label='mean')
    plt.step(data[1],mean_plu,where='post',color='blue',label='+3 SD')
    plt.step(data[1],mean_min,where='post',color='green',label='-3 SD')
    plt.title('Normally Distrubuted Random Variables (N = %d)' % N[i])
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    lgd = plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)
    plt.savefig('Q1-10Fig%d'%fc, bbox_extra_artists=(lgd,), bbox_inches='tight'); fc += 1

def f(x):
    t = lambda i: min(np.sin(i),0.7)
    return list(map(t,x))

#Helper function to process elements 
#of array passed to function f_inv.
def f_inv_el(y): 
    if y < 0.7:
        return np.arcsin(y)
    else:
        return np.random.rand(1)*(np.pi - 2*np.arcsin(0.7))+np.arcsin(0.7)
    
def f_inv(y):
    return np.array(list(map(f_inv_el,y)))

#Helper function to process 
#elements of array passed to function dydx.
def dydx_el(x):
    if np.arcsin(0.7) < x < np.pi - np.arcsin(0.7):
        
        #To keep nice scale in graph. Should return 0 here.
        return 0.05  
    else:
        return np.cos(x)
    
def dydx(x):
    return np.array(list(map(dydx_el,x)))

y = np.linspace(-0.99,0.70001,1000)
py = 1/(2*np.pi*(dydx(f_inv(y))))
uni = np.random.rand(1000)*2*np.pi
uniy = f(uni)

sns.distplot(uniy, hist=True, kde=False,norm_hist = True,\
             bins=20, color = 'blue',\
             hist_kws={'edgecolor':'black'},\
             kde_kws ={'label':'Kernel Density Estimate'})
plt.plot(y,py,color='red',label='Theoretical Transformed Distribution')
plt.title('Transformed Uniformly Distrubuted Random Variables {N = 1000} {y = min(sin(x), 0.7)}')
plt.xlabel('Value')
plt.ylabel('Count')
lgd = plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)

mean of means of 1000 samples of 1000 y variables = 0.9988552344303514

$\bar X =$ Mean of sample

$E\big[\bar X\big] = E\big[\frac{X_1 + X_2 + X_3 ... + X_n}{n}\big] $

$E\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{1}{n}E\big[ X_1 + X_2 + X_3 ... + X_n\big] $

$E\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{1}{n}\big(E\big[ X_1\big] +E\big[ X_2\big] +E\big[ X_3\big] ... + E\big[ X_n\big]\big) $

$E\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{1}{n}\big(\mu +\mu +\mu ... + \mu\big) $

$E\big[\bar X\big] = \mu$

$Var\big[\bar X\big] = Var\big[\frac{X_1 + X_2 + X_3 ... + X_n}{n}\big] $

$Var\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{1}{n^2}Var\big[X_1 + X_2 + X_3 ... + X_n\big]$

$Var\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{1}{n^2}(Var\big[X_1\big] + Var\big[X_2\big] + Var\big[X_3\big] ... + Var\big[X_n\big])$

$Var\big[\bar X\big] = \frac{n\sigma^2}{n^2} = \frac{\sigma^2}{n}$

alpha = [0.5,1.5,2] #(0,2) (alpha ≠ 1)
beta = [-1,-0.5,0,0.5,1] #[-1,+1]

N = 100000
U = np.random.uniform(-np.pi/2,np.pi/2,N)
V = np.random.exponential(1,N)
X_sets = []
bins = np.linspace(-60,60,401)
#Same set of random variables used for plots of all aplha/beta values
for i in range(len(alpha)):
    for j in range(len(beta)):
        
        b = (1/alpha[i])*np.arctan(beta[j]*np.tan(np.pi*alpha[i]/2))
        s = (1+(beta[j]**2)*(np.tan(np.pi*alpha[i]/2))**2)**(1/(2*alpha[i]))
        X = s*((np.sin(alpha[i]*(U + b)))/((np.cos(U))**(1/alpha[i])))*\
        ((np.cos(U-alpha[i]*(U+b)))/V)**((1-alpha[i])/alpha[i])
        X_sets.append((X,[i,j]))
        plt.figure()
        sns.distplot(X, hist=True, kde=False,\
             bins=bins, color = 'blue',\
             hist_kws={'edgecolor':'black'})
        plt.title('Difficult Density Random Variables (N = 100000) (alpha = %f, beta = %f)'\
                  % (alpha[i], beta[j]))
        plt.xlabel('Value')
        plt.ylabel('Count')
        plt.savefig('Q4-32Fig%d'%fc); fc += 1

    count0_5 = 0
    count1_5 = 0
    count1_999 = 0
    for j in range(N):
        if abs(X_sets[2][0][j]) > i: count0_5 += 1;
        if abs(X_sets[7][0][j]) > i: count1_5 += 1;
        if abs(X_sets[12][0][j]) > i: count1_999 += 1;
    alpha0_5[i] = count0_5/N
    alpha1_5[i] = count1_5/N
    alpha1_999[i] = count1_999/N

import statsmodels.api as sm 
bins2 = np.linspace(0,60,201)
h = np.histogram(X_sets[2][0],bins=bins2)

X = [np.log((h[1][i]+h[1][i+1])/2) for i in range(len(h[1])-1)]
Y = np.log(np.array(h[0]))
X1 = sm.add_constant(X)
reg = sm.OLS(Y, X1).fit()
